WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.630 --> 00:00:03.120
- Think about a project
you're working on right now.

2
00:00:03.120 --> 00:00:04.470
Ever felt like you've gone through

3
00:00:04.470 --> 00:00:07.230
the exact same motions before?

4
00:00:07.230 --> 00:00:09.300
I'm here to show you another way.

5
00:00:09.300 --> 00:00:11.100
And this method will not just help you

6
00:00:11.100 --> 00:00:12.600
with your current project,

7
00:00:12.600 --> 00:00:15.390
but it will also set you
up with a custom AI tool

8
00:00:15.390 --> 00:00:18.660
that you can go back
to time and time again.

9
00:00:18.660 --> 00:00:20.910
Sounds cool but also complicated?

10
00:00:20.910 --> 00:00:21.743
It's not.

11
00:00:21.743 --> 00:00:22.590
I'm Ammaar.

12
00:00:22.590 --> 00:00:25.680
I lead Product & Design
on Google AI Studio,

13
00:00:25.680 --> 00:00:27.360
the platform where you can work

14
00:00:27.360 --> 00:00:28.830
with the latest Google models

15
00:00:28.830 --> 00:00:30.720
and build your ideas.

16
00:00:30.720 --> 00:00:33.000
And AI has been a game changer

17
00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:35.280
for bringing my ideas to life.

18
00:00:35.280 --> 00:00:38.430
From books, animated shorts, coding games,

19
00:00:38.430 --> 00:00:41.460
podcasts with people
from the past, and more,

20
00:00:41.460 --> 00:00:44.340
AI has unleashed my creativity.

21
00:00:44.340 --> 00:00:45.690
Throughout your learning journey,

22
00:00:45.690 --> 00:00:49.230
you've been collaborating with
AI to amplify your skills.

23
00:00:49.230 --> 00:00:51.870
You can work with AI to brainstorm ideas,

24
00:00:51.870 --> 00:00:53.670
draft tailored communications,

25
00:00:53.670 --> 00:00:56.220
or get a first pass on a status report.

26
00:00:56.220 --> 00:00:58.260
You're having a conversation with AI

27
00:00:58.260 --> 00:01:00.510
to solve the challenge
right in front of you.

28
00:01:01.350 --> 00:01:04.500
Now, let's zoom out and
make even bigger strides.

29
00:01:04.500 --> 00:01:06.030
Across all of your work,

30
00:01:06.030 --> 00:01:08.250
what are the challenges
you are encountering

31
00:01:08.250 --> 00:01:10.260
time and time again?

32
00:01:10.260 --> 00:01:11.227
You might think to yourself,

33
00:01:11.227 --> 00:01:13.710
"I wish there was an app for this."

34
00:01:13.710 --> 00:01:14.910
Well, in this course,

35
00:01:14.910 --> 00:01:16.770
you're going to learn how to build it

36
00:01:16.770 --> 00:01:20.160
so that the next time you come
up against that challenge,

37
00:01:20.160 --> 00:01:22.830
you have a way to solve it fast.

38
00:01:22.830 --> 00:01:26.070
You're going to learn to
create custom shareable apps

39
00:01:26.070 --> 00:01:30.570
using AI that are designed by you for you.

40
00:01:30.570 --> 00:01:33.630
And this is the next
step in your AI journey,

41
00:01:33.630 --> 00:01:35.700
moving from being a user of AI

42
00:01:35.700 --> 00:01:39.810
to becoming a builder of your
own AI-powered solutions.

43
00:01:39.810 --> 00:01:41.640
To do so, I'm going to introduce you

44
00:01:41.640 --> 00:01:44.310
to something called vibe coding.

45
00:01:44.310 --> 00:01:46.470
It's a way you can use natural language

46
00:01:46.470 --> 00:01:49.260
to build software or apps with AI.

47
00:01:49.260 --> 00:01:51.330
You can then use that app

48
00:01:51.330 --> 00:01:54.030
to make it easier to get stuff done.

49
00:01:54.030 --> 00:01:57.480
For example, let's say you
have this kind of annoying task

50
00:01:57.480 --> 00:01:58.770
you always have to do,

51
00:01:58.770 --> 00:02:01.770
like resizing images for
your monthly newsletter.

52
00:02:01.770 --> 00:02:04.260
You wish you had an app
with a big Upload button

53
00:02:04.260 --> 00:02:06.150
that you could drop the images into

54
00:02:06.150 --> 00:02:10.350
and instantly get them back in
the size and format you need.

55
00:02:10.350 --> 00:02:11.730
You'd also love for that app

56
00:02:11.730 --> 00:02:13.800
to automatically rename the image files

57
00:02:13.800 --> 00:02:17.430
so that it follows your
team's naming conventions.

58
00:02:17.430 --> 00:02:18.360
Well, with vibe coding,

59
00:02:18.360 --> 00:02:21.090
you can build an app to
do all of those things

60
00:02:21.090 --> 00:02:22.710
just the way you need it.

61
00:02:22.710 --> 00:02:24.570
Vibe coding is a lot like prompting,

62
00:02:24.570 --> 00:02:27.480
it requires you to describe
exactly what you need,

63
00:02:27.480 --> 00:02:29.550
give AI details about your workflow,

64
00:02:29.550 --> 00:02:32.820
and help it understand
good results from bad ones.

65
00:02:32.820 --> 00:02:35.850
It can then attempt to
create your dream app.

66
00:02:35.850 --> 00:02:38.010
But how is this even possible?

67
00:02:38.010 --> 00:02:39.270
Well, when you vibe code,

68
00:02:39.270 --> 00:02:42.360
you're actually using
something called agentic AI,

69
00:02:42.360 --> 00:02:43.350
and this type of AI

70
00:02:43.350 --> 00:02:46.170
goes beyond just
responding to your prompts.

71
00:02:46.170 --> 00:02:48.750
It takes action on your behalf,

72
00:02:48.750 --> 00:02:51.720
but only under your
supervision, of course.

73
00:02:51.720 --> 00:02:53.310
After you describe what you need

74
00:02:53.310 --> 00:02:55.560
using normal, non-technical words,

75
00:02:55.560 --> 00:02:57.990
agentic AI handles all the techy stuff

76
00:02:57.990 --> 00:02:59.070
like writing code,

77
00:02:59.070 --> 00:03:00.150
building the interface,

78
00:03:00.150 --> 00:03:02.760
and making sure everything works together.

79
00:03:02.760 --> 00:03:03.660
And in this course,

80
00:03:03.660 --> 00:03:04.800
you'll learn how to vibe code

81
00:03:04.800 --> 00:03:07.890
to tackle some of the
challenges you face at work.

82
00:03:07.890 --> 00:03:09.930
First, you'll map out
your personal workflow

83
00:03:09.930 --> 00:03:12.630
and pinpoint exactly where a custom app

84
00:03:12.630 --> 00:03:15.060
would help you save the most time.

85
00:03:15.060 --> 00:03:17.340
Next, you'll see vibe coding in action.

86
00:03:17.340 --> 00:03:18.810
I'll walk you through different examples

87
00:03:18.810 --> 00:03:21.720
so you can see how it
works from start to finish.

88
00:03:21.720 --> 00:03:23.700
Finally, you'll build your own app.

89
00:03:23.700 --> 00:03:25.230
I'll guide you step by step

90
00:03:25.230 --> 00:03:27.690
and make sure you know how
to vibe code responsibly

91
00:03:27.690 --> 00:03:30.300
and troubleshoot common issues.

92
00:03:30.300 --> 00:03:33.210
You'll find out how to
evaluate the code AI developed,

93
00:03:33.210 --> 00:03:34.140
own the results,

94
00:03:34.140 --> 00:03:36.630
and maintain your app over time.

95
00:03:36.630 --> 00:03:38.010
All of this will help make sure

96
00:03:38.010 --> 00:03:40.950
you create an app that actually works.

97
00:03:40.950 --> 00:03:42.300
And by the end of the course,

98
00:03:42.300 --> 00:03:44.820
you'll have a method
you can repeatedly use

99
00:03:44.820 --> 00:03:49.110
to identify ways Gemini,
Google AI Studio and NotebookLM

100
00:03:49.110 --> 00:03:51.060
can help you in your job,

101
00:03:51.060 --> 00:03:53.520
and you'll have the skills
and confidence you need

102
00:03:53.520 --> 00:03:54.990
to create a custom app

103
00:03:54.990 --> 00:03:57.930
that can handle some of your larger tasks.

104
00:03:57.930 --> 00:03:59.790
If you're ready to start building,

105
00:03:59.790 --> 00:04:00.623
let's jump in.